How to choose the mattress and somier: women and men look for different things
Nothing of a pompous frame for the bed; what really entrusts its quality to a good bed is the surface to lie down, i.e. the mattress and somier.
First of all, they must be complemented perfectly to suit specific users.
During the election, numerous elements come into play, including the weight, height, health status and sex of the owner.
The type of interior in which the mattress and somier is located is also important.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cabin that does not usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they "heat" more slowly.
In addition, they usually weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattresses.
Therefore, it is necessary to turn them around more often.
If the channels of the center are not properly ventilated and, above, they are located on a firm base, they keep moisture inside.
When choosing a bed, it also influences the habits.
Those who have spent a lot of time abroad often use a very high mattress with a soft layer and will have trouble feeling good on a lower and harder surface.
"Almost all the hockey players who came back from the NHL complained that they didn't sleep as well here."
"For his jaw-dropping shoulders, heels and hips needed mattresses with a soft viscoelastic layer."
“These types of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes who have time problems with the nervous system, so they get bad information from the joints and the skin,” explains Sylva Hadamczikov<0xC3><0xA1>, who specializes in padded furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italians Magniflex, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You don’t have to be an NHL player to be able to appreciate the viscoelastics.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
Optimizes its rigidity and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to its body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it will not turn around as after a hard game.
He just sleeps better.
Viscoelastic also acts as a protection against wounds.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to its height the length of its feet, i.e., between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, for example singles, a minimum of 120 to 140 cm is recommended.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, a simple rule can be applied to calculate the width: when lying face up, you should have your hands comfortably bent towards the elbows," advises engineer Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>, expert at Cechu <0xC4><0x8D>aloun<0xC3><0xAD>k<0xC5><0xAF> to decorators, who has been dealing with the problem of healthy sleeping and erectile issues for many years.
In the double rooms, everyone needs their own dreamer and mattress, so during the purchase you need to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the sleepers at different heights, which is not always possible in all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, models with spring interior a minimum of 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that adapts to shapes and softens.
“By touching it with your hand or by settling on the mattress, you certainly shouldn’t notice the springs,” warns Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>.
Each mattress requires a certain type of sommelier.
The fully padded bedrooms, in which the mattress and base are like Siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
The mattresses breathe poorly and you can’t wash your cover, which is often done today.
And, since we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat each night, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a large (and congested) screen.
For this reason, experts reject slogans that speak of a mattress life of up to 25 years or even a lifetime warranty.
However, everything has a but.
That’s why sellers give a tip: in mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, take care of cleaning and washing the case carefully, but better add a mattress protector that can be easily removed and washed.
Although mattress covers are currently manufactured with zipper closure throughout their perimeter, so when opening them they are left in two parts (something very important for washing and the size of the washing machine!), their manipulation in the larger models (and for one person) when lifting the mattress can look like a fight between a weight and a weight.
In bed, instead of a dreamer, do you have a firm table?
Never!
As much for beds designed for one night visits.
However, you should make (if you do not already have them) ventilation holes in the table and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For non-articulated sheet sommeliers containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g., a combination of latex and coconut fiber) can be used, although it is always better to have a sommelier with a greater number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the sheets of the lumbar zone can be adjusted and reinforced.
Articulated sheet lugs should not be used with a spring mattress, as it does not react to reclination.
In addition to adjusting the rigidity of the sheets, shoulder protection can also be used.
It is a special fixation of the sheets that allows you to press or even tilt the sheets in such a way that they perfectly "round" the shoulders during sleep.
For men who have very wide shoulders, this is something very important.
They are even remembered by mattress manufacturers who, in the "males", began to use a softer area precisely around the shoulders.
They also remember women, for whom they put a softer area around the hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are sommeliers with cross-structure or tablets with the so-called multitortion damping.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the voltage is reduced.
It should also be borne in mind that even if you use the right mattress and somier, if you use a bad pillow (large and "soft"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow should hold the head and the corners can only reach to the shoulders, so that the muscles of them can be relaxed.
The appropriate size recommended is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying on the side, the pillow should be at the same level (when combined with the shoulder cushion or softer area of the mattress) as the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses have something to do, it seems, with original mattresses filled with straw.
Manufacturers continue to use, more and more often, natural materials or, at least, mixtures.
In fact, organic mattresses are fashionable.
Oil-based raw materials, with which polyurethane foam is manufactured, are filled with natural oils, for example castor or soy.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soy.
“Biological, in the case of mattresses, means that the center is made only of materials of natural origin,” explains Petr Va<0xC5><0xA1><0xC3><0xAD><0xC4><0x8D>ek of Tropico Plus.
Also, natural substances are used during the manufacture of the mattress cover, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also opt for microcapsules, which release a fresh scent to forest or lavender.
There are also differences between men and women.
While men "refresh" with plant extracts of breeze, so that the mattress cover absorbs heat and cools the body, women prefer to "warm" the cover.
Red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so that women feel more warmth.
The favorites right now?
Cold foam mattresses, which are more porous, with an adapted cell structure, which makes them more permeable than normal polyurethane and offer more permeability.
The combination of various cold foam and viscoelastic rigidities makes it possible to manufacture mattresses from various areas that know perfectly where the head, shoulders and heels go.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand crowns up.
Those who perform a therapeutic function usually have a lower VAT, since they are considered as health care.
The first to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It is difficult to save on mattresses and sommeliers.
Sometimes the offers of manufacturers or sellers can be approved, which sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with a Memory memory foam attached to the case for 11,990 crowns.
The second one is available for free.
The era of viscoelastics with an open cell structure and high density began with the "cosmic" material of Tempur.
It initially emerged as material for NASA, because during the takeoffs astronauts were subjected to a huge overload.
Tempur softens with heat and hardens with cold.
Therefore, the warm human body exerts a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent sores from occurring, although also to improve comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foam is not only used in mattresses, but also for sanitary products, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and relieve them, as well as their circulation.
National manufacturers, for example, use Eucatherm C or Twinsaver foam and the like.
More and more parents use people tracking devices to control their children
The fear of children leads more and more people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for vehicle tracking, can also track people’s movement and thus contribute, for example, in the case of the disappearance of the nine-year-old girl Ani<0xC4><0x8D>ka Janatkov<0xC3><0xA1>.
At the moment the device is about the size of a box of candles, but will soon be reduced to the size of a watch.
Many people were afraid of the case of the missing Ani<0xC4><0x8D>ka and began to report on the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
“We’re all trying to tell ourselves that it’s not about spying, but another way to lessen the chances of a tragedy,” said Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
“I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example if they are put in someone’s pocket without their knowledge, but we have not yet encountered such cases.”
“Most customers actually buy it for security reasons,” adds Pilin.
In their opinion, children should always know what "cajita" is for and how it is used in case of an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bo<0xC4><0x8D>kov<0xC3><0xA1> warns about the fact that if the child does not want to carry it, he will simply throw it away.
“Even younger children show great creativity when it comes to intentionally losing certain things if they want to prevent them from controlling them.”
“In the past, parents relied heavily on mobile phones, but these could be turned off as easily as the tracking device,” Bo<0xC4><0x8D>kov<0xC3><0xA1> says.
In your opinion, it is questionable whether in case of attack such a device is really useful.
“If it’s a ready-made kidnapping, the author will almost always check if the child carries some kind of electronic device that can reveal his location.”
"Now it's the phone."
“As the use of tracking devices expands, it will also look for them, as their sale will undoubtedly be carried out with a lot of publicity.”
“In such cases, criminals always go one step ahead of the police,” says the psychologist.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the case of an improvised attack of a pedophile.
According to Robert <0xC4><0x8C>ech of RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can be helpful.
"The device can be configured to send the position regularly after a certain period."
"If you suffer damage, at least it will facilitate the last position of the person in question."
“The most expensive devices carry an integrated tilt meter, so if the person simply slips and remains stationary, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question,” says <0xC4><0x8C>ech.
In your opinion, such a service can be obtained even with mobile phones with navigation, in which only special software must be installed.
The problem with current tracking units is that at the moment they are devices that are similar in size to a screen box or smaller mobile phones.
Therefore, they can be lost.
According to Pilin of Macro Weil, for this reason tests are currently being carried out with devices that look like a digital clock.
"In addition, they will have the added advantage that a potential attacker may not identify the device."
“Or identifying it after a certain time, which can make the police gain time,” he adds.
Although tracking devices are carried on the wrist or hanging, they will continue to use the same technology that is used for tracking vehicles.
It is the verification of the position with a GPS system (which is used in the usual navigation in the car) combined with the function of a mobile phone communicating the current position.
The army has enough wicks to encircle the whole of the Czech Republic, but they only last two years.
