"First, the external qualities of the candidates will determine whether they meet the requirements, such as height, weight, facial features, etc."
Then comes the temperament "and the inner qualities."
The female Chengguan are like florists, he said, and added, "in addition to being florists, they will have other responsibilities."
Zheng Lihua, deputy director of the district city administration office, is not looking forward to supporting that description.
But he noted that the height requirements were standards in many Chinese job ads for both sexes.
Then comes the demand for harmonious facial features.
