Surely, the disabled or disfigured should not be presented.
“We cannot allow a person to cuddle or a jowl to come to work here,” Mr. Zheng said.
“Your image would not be good.”
Liu Yi, who patrols Baoguang Square near a monastery, is 22 years old, with his cheeks colored and a subtly curved mouth.
She doesn’t think the accent on her looks is sexist, she said.
"Do you think I look sexy in this uniform?" he asked with a sardonic look.
The 21-year-old co-worker, Xu Yang, said, “Our work should present the image of the city.”
They also don’t object to their work at a given time, they said, because they harbor larger career ambitions than simply evicting sellers in the alleys where they are supposed to circumscribe their business.
